headline: Dell (NYSE:DELL) Reports Q3 CY2025 In Line With Expectations
summary: Computer hardware and IT solutions company Dell (NYSE:DELL) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 10.8% year on year to $27.01 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $31.5 billion, coming in 14.6% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.59 per share was 4.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Dell misses Q3 revenue estimates while raising full-year forecast

Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton dives into the hardware and computer company's latest earnings release and its fourth quarter and full-year forecasts.
